  <main id="main" class="container" role="main">
    <article id="overview" aria-labelledby="overview-title">
      <h2 id="overview-title">Overview</h2>
      <p class="note" role="note">This page demonstrates: <strong>semantic HTML</strong>, <strong>well-structured content</strong> (lists, tables, media), and a <strong>complete, accessible HTML5 form</strong> using required attributes, placeholders, autocomplete, readonly, patterns, ranges, and native validation.</p>

      <section id="content" aria-labelledby="content-title">
        <h3 id="content-title">Structured Content</h3>
        <div class="grid cols-2">
          <section>
            <h4>Key Points (List)</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Semantic landmarks: <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;article&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code></li>
              <li>Accessible labels and captions</li>
              <li>Native HTML5 validation (types, patterns, min/max)</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Definitions (DL)</h4>
            <dl>
              <dt>Readonly</dt>
              <dd>An input that is submitted but not editable by the user.</dd>
              <dt>Autocomplete</dt>
              <dd>Hints the browser on what kind of data to auto-fill.</dd>
            </dl>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Comparison (Table)</h4>
            <table>
              <caption>Input attribute highlights</caption>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th scope="col">Attribute</th>
                  <th scope="col">Purpose</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>required</code></td>
                  <td>Prevents form submission without a value.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>pattern</code></td>
                  <td>Enforces a regex format (e.g., phone).</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>min</code> / <code>max</code> / <code>step</code></td>
                  <td>Constrain numeric/date inputs.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><code>readonly</code></td>
                  <td>Displays fixed data that still submits.</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </section>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="media" aria-labelledby="media-title" class="example-media">
